{
  "verses": [
    {
      "verse_num": 6,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "This parable spake Jesus unto them: but they understood not what things they were which he spake unto them."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 7,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then said Jesus unto them again,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 19,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "There was a division therefore again among the Jews for these sayings."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Division Among the Jews"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 20,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "He hath a devil, and is mad; why hear ye him?",
          "speaker": "Some Jews"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 21,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "These are not the words of him that hath a devil. Can a devil open the eyes of the blind?",
          "speaker": "Others"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 22,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And it was at Jerusalem the feast of the dedication, and it was winter."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": [
        "Feast of Dedication"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 23,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And Jesus walked in the temple in Solomon's porch."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 24,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then came the Jews round about him, and said unto him,"
        },
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "How long dost thou make us to doubt? If thou be the Christ, tell us plainly.",
          "speaker": "Jews"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 25,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jesus answered them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 31,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then the Jews took up stones again to stone him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 32,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jesus answered them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 33,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "For a good work we stone thee not; but for blasphemy; and because that thou, being a man, makest thyself God.",
          "speaker": "Jews"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 34,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Jesus answered them,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 39,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Therefore they sought again to take him: but he escaped out of their hand,"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 40,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And went away again beyond Jordan into the place where John at first baptized; and there he abode."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 41,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "speech",
          "text": "John did no miracle: but all things that John spake of this man were true.",
          "speaker": "People"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": 42,
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "And many believed on him there."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": [],
      "heading": []
    }
  ]
}